## âœï¸ Hands-On Exercise:

**Safeguards I Would Implement in OpenMRS:**

- **Administrative Safeguard**:  
  â€œEstablish a formal policy to review OpenMRS audit logs weekly for suspicious activity.â€  
  _Why_: This ensures early detection of misuse and reinforces accountability.

- **Technical Safeguard**:  
  â€œEnable two-factor authentication (2FA) for all OpenMRS users accessing ePHI.â€  
  _Why_: Adds an essential security layer beyond passwords, mitigating account compromise risk.

These actions directly support HIPAAâ€™s goals of **confidentiality, integrity, and availability** of patient data.

