## ğŸ’¡ Reflection:

HIPAAâ€™s three safeguard categories cover all bases â€” **people, places, and technology**.  
In a **small clinic**, **technical safeguards** might be the most challenging due to limited IT resources or budget. But skipping any category creates gaps. Even perfect encryption won't help if someone shares credentials or walks away from an unlocked terminal.

Each layer supports the other. HIPAAâ€™s structure pushes organizations to think **holistically**, not just about tools or rules in isolation â€” and thatâ€™s why it remains a cornerstone of healthcare cybersecurity.

